<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 13837/2.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Dodge</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-06-04"><hi rend="italic">June 4,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Bacon acknowledges his telegram of June 3, and requests him to advise
                            department immediately upon the arrest of Bailey and <pb facs="0578" n="476" xml:id="pg_476"/> detention of the <hi rend="italic">Goldsboro</hi>. Mr. Bacon instructs Mr. Dodge to ascertain what
                            formalities the Honduranean Government will require before turning
                            Bailey and the vessel over to the United States Government.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>